type: web_research
title: Ollama Anthropic API + RouteLLM + Local Coding Models Research (Feb 2026)
source: "Multiple web sources - Ollama docs, LMSYS, OpenRouter, various benchmarks"
key_insights[12]: Ollama v0.14.0+ supports Anthropic Messages API - Claude Code can connect directly to local models,Ollama v0.15+ adds 'ollama launch' command for zero-config Claude Code setup,"Supported features: streaming, tool calling, system prompts, extended thinking, vision","NOT supported: token counting, tool_choice forcing, prompt caching, batch processing, PDF blocks","Top local coding models: Qwen3-Coder (30B/480B), GLM-4.7 (73.8% SWE-bench), DeepSeek-Coder-V2","Qwen3-Coder-Next: 70.6% SWE-bench with only 3B active params (80B MoE), runs on Mac","GLM-4.7: 73.8% SWE-bench, 66.7% SWE-bench Multilingual, available on Ollama","RouteLLM: 4 routers (mf, sw_ranking, bert, causal_llm), up to 85% cost reduction",RouteLLM BERT classifier trained on 55K Chatbot Arena preference comparisons,"DeepSeek V3.2 on OpenRouter: $0.27/M input, $0.41/M output, 164K context","SWE-bench reality: 75-80% verified drops to 55-58% on fresh tasks, 15-23% on enterprise","Cloud leaders: Claude Opus 4.6 (80.8%), GPT-5.1 Codex (77.9%), Gemini 3 Pro (76.2%)"
findings[8]: "Ollama Anthropic API config: ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN=ollama, ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434",ollama launch claude - zero config setup for Claude Code (v0.15+),"Recommended: 32K+ context, 64K optimal for coding, 23GB VRAM at full context","RouteLLM install: pip install routellm[serve,eval]","RouteLLM threshold calibration: python -m routellm.calibrate_threshold --routers mf","Mac M-series: 7B@20tok/s on M2, 8B@28tok/s on M3 Pro, 70B@5-8tok/s","Qwen3-Coder 30B: 19GB download, 3.3B active params","GLM-4.7 Flash: 59.2% SWE-bench, ~80 tok/s in 4-bit quant"
